s:1150:"<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;"><strong>Course Completion Requirements: Reading Comprehensio</strong><strong>n</strong></span><br /></p><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">To complete the <strong>Reading Comprehension</strong> course, you need to:</p><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ol><li><strong>Complete All Modules:</strong> Successfully finish each module, covering key topics such as literal comprehension, inferential comprehension, and critical reading.</li><li><strong>Pass Quizzes and Assessments</strong>: Achieve a passing score on all quizzes and assessments to demonstrate your understanding of the material.</li><li><strong>Participate in Discussions:</strong> Engage in course module discussions and activities to apply your knowledge and interact with peers.</li><li><strong>Achieve a Minimum Grade:</strong> Attain the minimum grade set to ensure mastery of reading comprehension skills.</li></ol><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">Upon meeting these requirements, you will have demonstrated a strong grasp of reading comprehension, enabling you to effectively understand, analyze, and interpret texts.</p>";